.TH "xdr_stream_decode_string_dup" 9 "xdr_stream_decode_string_dup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xdr_stream_decode_string_dup \- Decode and duplicate variable length string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" xdr_stream_decode_string_dup
.BI "(struct xdr_stream *xdr "  ","
.BI "char **str "  ","
.BI "size_t maxlen "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xdr" 12
pointer to xdr_stream
.IP "str" 12
location to store pointer to string
.IP "maxlen" 12
maximum acceptable string length
.IP "gfp_flags" 12
GFP mask to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return values:
On success, returns length of NUL-terminated string stored in *\fIptr\fP
-EBADMSG on XDR buffer overflow
-EMSGSIZE if the size of the string would exceed \fImaxlen\fP
-ENOMEM on memory allocation failure
